  "prompt": "Do all MSI laptop's steel series keyboards light up?",
  "response": "Not all MSI laptops with SteelSeries keyboards have RGB lighting or backlighting. MSI offers a range of laptops with SteelSeries keyboards, and the lighting features vary depending on the model and its positioning in the lineup.\n\nHere\u2019s a breakdown:\n\n1. **Low to Mid-Range Models**: Some entry-level or mid-range MSI laptops may have SteelSeries keyboards with **single-color backlighting** (e.g., white or red) or no backlighting at all. This depends on the specific model and its intended audience.\n\n2. **High-End and Gaming Models**: Most high-end MSI gaming laptops, especially those in the **GE, GP, GS, and GT series**, feature SteelSeries keyboards with **per-key RGB lighting**. These keyboards allow for customizable lighting effects and synchronization with other RGB components in the system.\n\n3. **Customization**: On laptops with RGB lighting, you can typically customize the lighting via MSI\u2019s **SteelSeries Engine** software, which offers a variety of effects, colors, and profiles.\n\n### How to Check:\nWhen considering an MSI laptop, check the product specifications or product description to confirm whether the SteelSeries keyboard includes lighting and, if so, what type (single-color or RGB). If you\u2019re unsure, you can also consult reviews or contact MSI support for clarification.\n\nIn summary, while many MSI laptops with SteelSeries keyboards do light up, especially in the gaming segment, it\u2019s not a universal feature across all models. Always verify the specific model\u2019s features before purchasing.",
